textAfterTable: May 18, 2010 - 9:02am -- braswell Registration for summer classes at Pearl River Community College Forrest County Center will be held from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Thursday.Students should come to the multi purpose room in Building 5.Summer registration on the Poplarville campus will be held from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Thursday and Friday and from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. May 24-28. Students should come to the admissions office in the Ted J. Alexander Administration Building.Night classes begin Monday, May 24. Day classes begin Tuesday, June 1.Students who received Pell Grants during the fall or spring semesters may be eligible for another award for summer classes.
